--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY & OBJECTIVES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The SkyGuard AI project is an end-to-end software application designed to solve the challenges of autonomous UAV mission planning, route visualization, and pre-flight compliance auditing. By utilizing a modular multi-agent workflow, the application parses natural language goals, plans geometric search or patrol paths, verifies safety rules (altitude ceiling, takeoff/landing presence, waypoint distance, geofences, and battery capacity), and outputs formatted documentation.

This system guarantees that no flight path is initiated without verification of local airspace compliance standards, protecting drone hardware and preventing illegal airspace violations.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE & INTEGRATED AGENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The software architecture is decoupled into five distinct, specialized agent models implemented in Python:

2.1 Mission Understanding Agent
------------------------------
- Purpose: Parses plain text commands (e.g., "Plan a 15 min surveillance at 60 meters") into parameters.
- Technologies: Google Gemini API (gemini-1.5-flash) with an offline regular expression (regex) fallback parser.
- Extracted Fields: mission_type, target_altitude, duration_window, route_pattern, home coordinates.

2.2 Waypoint Planner Agent
-------------------------
- Purpose: Generates exact geographic nodes (lat/lon/alt) based on target geometric profiles.
- Profiles: Square patrol, circular orbits, perimeter scans, and lawn-mower grid mapping.
- Sequence Rules: Automatically injects MAV_CMD_NAV_TAKEOFF at index 0 and MAV_CMD_NAV_RETURN_TO_LAUNCH (RTL) or LAND at the final index.

2.3 Safety Compliance Agent
--------------------------
- Purpose: Audits telemetry parameters and coordinates against 7 strict airspace rules.
- Implementation: Re-projects latitude/longitude coordinates into a localized metric flat Cartesian plane to eliminate the degree-meter aspect distortion at varying latitudes.
- Intersections: Uses Shapely LineString to detect segment-restricted zone intersections rather than checking point waypoints alone.

2.4 Correction Agent
--------------------
- Purpose: Auto-corrects unsafe flight parameters.
- Polygon Geofences: Employs Shapely boundary projection normal vectors to project waypoints out of polygon no-fly zones by a 15.0m buffer.
- Circle Geofences: Computes radial vectors from the circle center and shifts points along the outward bearing.

2.5 Report Generation Agent
--------------------------
- Purpose: Compiles styled HTML dashboards, CSV waypoint lists, PDF records, and QGroundControl-compatible JSON flight plans.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. SAFETY RULES AND MATHEMATICAL FORMULAS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The auditor enforces 7 safety compliance standards (R1 to R7):

- R1 (Altitude Limit): Target altitude <= 80.0 meters.
- R2 (Takeoff Node): Waypoints[0] action == "takeoff".
- R3 (Landing/RTL Node): Waypoints[-1] action in ["rtl", "land"].
- R4 (Geofence Check): Waypoint points & line segments must not intersect circular/polygon restricted zones.
- R5 (Max Leg Length): Distance between consecutive waypoints <= 500 meters.
- R6 (Flight Duration): Duration <= 30.0 minutes.
- R7 (Battery Check): Estimated battery consumption < 80.0%.

3.1 Physics-Based Battery Model
------------------------------
Unlike static linear models, SkyGuard AI implements a multi-stage energy consumption calculation:
- UAV Mass: 1.5 kg
- Battery Capacity: 90 Wh (standard 4S LiPo battery)
- Cruise Speed: 10 m/s (Cruise Power: 120W)
- Climb Speed: 4 m/s (Climb Power: 215W)
- Descent Speed: 2 m/s (Descent Power: 115W)
- Hover Power: 130W
The flight phases are calculated individually:
  - Takeoff Ascent energy: E_climb = P_climb * (Altitude / V_climb) / 3600
  - Transition Cruise energy: E_cruise = P_cruise * (Haversine_Distance / V_cruise) / 3600
  - Landing Descent energy: E_descend = P_descend * (Altitude / V_descend) / 3600
  - Remaining hover time energy: E_hover = P_hover * Max(0, Planned_Duration - Total_Flight_Time) / 3600
  - Battery Percent = (Total_Energy_Wh / 90.0) * 100

